INSERT INTO `recipe` VALUES (470,'Vanilla Milkshake','vanilla ice cream, whole milk, white sugar, vanilla extract','Place a tall glass in the freezer for 5 minutes so the milkshake stays cold on contact. | Add the vanilla ice cream, whole milk, white sugar, and vanilla extract to a blender jar. | Blend on low for 10 seconds to break up the ice cream, then blend on high for 20–30 seconds until smooth, thick, and glossy; stop and scrape down the sides with a spatula if needed, then blend 5 seconds more. | Pour into the chilled glass immediately; the milkshake should mound slightly before settling and be thick enough to drink through a wide straw.','[\"1½ cups\",\"½ cup\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\"]',520,'vanilla-milkshake-recipe.png','A classic milkshake blended until thick and smooth, finished with vanilla and a small amount of sugar.',10,1,6,2,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',7,'EASY','United States'),(471,'Buttermilk Pancakes','flour, buttermilk, egg, canola oil, baking powder, white sugar, salt','Set a 20 cm nonstick skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes, until a drop of water sizzles and evaporates quickly; lightly brush the surface with a thin film of canola oil. | Whisk flour, baking powder, white sugar, and salt in a medium bowl for 20 seconds to evenly distribute the leavening. | In a small bowl, whisk buttermilk and egg for 20 seconds until smooth, then pour into the dry ingredients and whisk just until no dry flour remains; let the batter rest 5 minutes until it looks slightly thicker and small bubbles appear on the surface. | Spoon the batter into the hot skillet in 2 rounds (about ¼ cup batter each) and cook 2–3 minutes, until bubbles rise and pop on top and the edges look set and slightly dry. | Flip with a thin spatula and cook 1–2 minutes more, until the second side is golden-brown and the centers spring back when lightly pressed; repeat with the remaining batter, brushing the pan with a little more canola oil only if it looks dry.','[\"½ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"1 large\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'pancakes-recipe.png','Classic stovetop pancakes with a tender crumb and lightly browned edges.',10,1,8,4,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',18,'EASY','United States'),(473,'Chicken Caesar Wrap','boneless skinless chicken breast, large flour tortilla, romaine lettuce, chopped, Parmesan cheese, finely grated, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, finely grated, olive oil, salt, black pepper','Pat the chicken dry with paper towels, then season both sides evenly with the salt and black pepper. | Heat a 25 cm non-stick skillet over medium-high heat until hot (about 190°C surface temp), add 1 tsp olive oil, and swirl to coat. Lay in the chicken and cook 4–5 minutes on the first side until golden brown; flip and cook 3–5 minutes more until the thickest part reaches 74°C and the juices run clear. Transfer to a plate and rest 3 minutes, then slice into thin strips. | In a medium bowl, whisk the mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and grated garlic until smooth and glossy; this is the Caesar dressing. | Add the chopped romaine and 1½ tbsp of the Parmesan to the bowl and toss until the leaves look lightly coated and no dressing pools at the bottom. | Warm the tortilla in the same skillet over medium heat for 15–20 seconds per side until pliable with a few light toast marks, then set it on a cutting board. | Pile the dressed romaine down the center of the to','[\"1 small (about 120 g)\",\"1 piece\",\"1½ cups\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"1 clove\",\"2 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',620,'popular-real-lunch-recipe-recipe.png','A classic lunch wrap with warm chicken, crisp romaine, Parmesan, and Caesar dressing wrapped in a toasted tortilla.',8,0,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',20,'EASY','United States'),(474,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, green bell pepper, thinly sliced, red onion, thinly sliced, feta cheese, cut into 1 cm slabs, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Set out a medium bowl and a cutting board; cut the tomato and cucumber into 2 cm chunks, slice the bell pepper into thin strips, and slice the red onion very thin (use a knife or mandoline carefully). | Add the tomato, cucumber, bell pepper, and red onion to the bowl; add the olives and toss gently for 10 seconds so the vegetables stay chunky and don’t release too much juice. | In a small bowl, whisk the extra-virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper for 15–20 seconds until the dressing looks slightly thickened and evenly mixed. | Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently with a spoon for about 15 seconds, just until the vegetables look glossy and lightly coated. | Lay the feta slabs on top; let the salad stand at room temperature for 2 minutes so the oregano perfumes the oil, then serve immediately while the vegetables are crisp and the feta holds its shape.','[\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"¼ medium\",\"¼ small\",\"50 g\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',430,'popular-real-salad-recipe-recipe.png','A classic Greek salad with cucumber, tomato, bell pepper, red onion, olives, and feta, dressed with olive oil and oregano.',9,0,5,8,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece'),(475,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','chocolate chips, flour, unsalted butter, softened, brown sugar, egg yolk, white sugar, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Heat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with baking paper. | In a medium bowl, mix the softened unsalted butter, brown sugar, and white sugar with a fork for 45–60 seconds until smooth and glossy. | Mix in the egg yolk and vanilla extract until fully combined and slightly thickened, about 20 seconds. | Add the flour, baking soda, and salt. Stir with a spoon just until no dry flour remains; 